articles.author: Bailey Rahn
articles.text:
It's Friday, which means it's time to kick off the weekend with some tempting new strains! This week, we've got some vicious new varieties like Kill Bill and Viper, as well as the flavorful California Grapefruit, the energizing White Haze, and the potent Tokyo OG. You suggested them, and now it's time to complete these strains with your review. Be sure to also check out which of these strains are available near you by navigating to their strain pages and clicking "Availability." You just might discover a new favorite!
   1. Kill Bill
Characteristics of Kill Bill:

Hybrid strain
Cross between Killer Queen and Willy's Wonder
Breeder: Reservoir Seeds
Skunky, pine aroma
Cerebral energy coupled with full-body relaxation
May help patients treating stress, pain, and appetite loss
Indoor flowering time of 7 to 8 weeks

   2. Viper
Characteristics of Viper:

95% sativa
Cross between Burmese and Mexican landrace strains
Breeder: Reeferman Seeds
Spicy, citrus aroma
Buzzing, active cerebral effects
Indoor flowering time of 10 weeks

   3. California Grapefruit
Characteristics of California Grapefruit:

Mostly indica
Cross between Northern Lights, Skunk #1, and Afghani
Breeder: DNA Genetics
Sweet, earthy, grapefruit aroma
Heavily relaxing with slow onset
May help patients treating pain, insomnia, and muscle tension
Indoor flowering time of 52 to 63 days

   4. Tokyo OG
Characteristics of Tokyo OG:

Hybrid strain
OG Kush phenotype
Lemon, pine, and diesel aroma
Relaxing indica effects
May help patients treating anxiety, stress, and pain

   5. White Haze
Characteristics of White Haze:

70/30 sativa-dominant strain
Haze hybrid
Breeder: Sensi Seeds
Spicy aroma
Lightweight, lofty buzz balanced by comfortable relaxation
Indoor flowering time of 60 days
articles.title: New Strains Alert: Kill Bill, Viper, California Grapefruit, Tokyo OG, and White Haze

description: Tokyo OG, originating from Northern California, is yet another rendition of the famous OG Kush hybrid. This cutting preserves the traditional OG aroma that blends lemon and pine with a distinctive diesel bite. Indica characteristics shine through in this phenotype, offering a dense, chunky bud structure and relaxing effects that help many consumers put to sleep anxiety, pain, and stress. However, novices beware: Tokyo OG oftentimes boasts a staggeringly high THC content that can exacerbate anxiety rather than alleviate it.

highlightedReviews.text: This is a beautiful OG hybrid, indica dominant female. Her smell alone will knock you on your ass. The taste is a frosty og with a subtle bite to the burn but not as sharp As some SFV  can be. A very dense smoke and quite the lung filler. Two hits from a glass pipe and the room is full of smoke and it's couch lock city for 2 hours plus. This strain is a SoCal dispensarie's riserva Pravda and it's always tested above 21 percent total thc and thca. A true example of conesiour genetics. Crystals cover the stocky and dense buds and just from its scent you know it's hiding a treasure trove of indica inspired relaxation within it's folds of OG goodness. Only side effect is a severe case of the munchies, a real gut filler.
after this one hit wonder the phrase "mood elevator" came quickly to mind.......when i returned to the dispensary, i ordered another eighth, well done

name: Tokyo OG
